1
00:00:02.544 --> 00:00:06.548 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
SISKO: <i>Captain's Personal Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 51247.5.</i>

2
00:00:06.631 --> 00:00:09.801 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>It's been a week since</i>
<i>our return to Deep Space 9,</i>

3
00:00:09.884 --> 00:00:12.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>but the mood</i>
<i>of celebration continues.</i>

4
00:00:12.470 --> 00:00:14.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We're still at war,</i>
<i>and the station's</i>

5
00:00:14.472 --> 00:00:16.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>been designated headquarters</i>
<i>for the Ninth Fleet.</i>

6
00:00:16.641 --> 00:00:18.685 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That, plus</i>
<i>our strategic position</i>

7
00:00:18.768 --> 00:00:20.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>guarding the wormhole,</i>
<i>makes DS9</i>

8
00:00:20.937 --> 00:00:22.522 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>one of the most</i>
<i>tempting targets</i>

9
00:00:22.605 --> 00:00:24.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>in the entire quadrant.</i>

10
00:00:24.315 --> 00:00:28.028 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>But for now, at least,</i>
<i>the war seems very far away.</i>

11
00:00:34.659 --> 00:00:36.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Morning.
-Good morning.

12
00:00:36.202 --> 00:00:37.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good morning.

13
00:00:37.495 --> 00:00:38.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Morning, Major.

14
00:00:38.872 --> 00:00:40.707 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good morning, Captain.

15
00:00:40.790 --> 00:00:42.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you know
how much I missed

16
00:00:42.417 --> 00:00:43.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
hearing you say that?

17
00:00:43.835 --> 00:00:45.837 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you know how much
I hated saying

18
00:00:45.920 --> 00:00:46.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Good morning, Dukat"?

19
00:00:47.046 --> 00:00:47.964 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can imagine.

20
00:00:48.047 --> 00:00:49.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's on the agenda?

21
00:00:49.507 --> 00:00:52.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh, USS <i>Potemkin</i>
has completed her repairs

22
00:00:52.343 --> 00:00:54.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and is rejoining the fleet
later today.

23
00:00:54.471 --> 00:00:56.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Exeter, Sutherland</i>
and <i>Agaki</i>

24
00:00:56.181 --> 00:00:58.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
have submitted
resupply requests

25
00:00:58.099 --> 00:00:59.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and there are
about 1,000 messages

26
00:01:00.060 --> 00:01:01.436 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
from Starfleet Command

27
00:01:01.519 --> 00:01:03.396 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
awaiting your "eyes-only"
attention.

28
00:01:03.480 --> 00:01:04.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Anything else?

29
00:01:04.939 --> 00:01:07.067 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
General Martok is waiting
in your office.

30
00:01:07.150 --> 00:01:08.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, I'll start
with the General.

31
00:01:09.027 --> 00:01:10.236 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought you would.

32
00:01:12.655 --> 00:01:15.200 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have I mentioned
that it's good to be home?

33
00:01:16.743 --> 00:01:18.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Once or twice.

34
00:01:20.371 --> 00:01:22.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right.

35
00:01:25.877 --> 00:01:28.171 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You knew about this,
didn't you?

36
00:01:28.254 --> 00:01:29.839 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I had a pretty good idea.

37
00:01:29.923 --> 00:01:32.842 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you did nothing to stop it.

38
00:01:32.926 --> 00:01:34.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No.

39
00:01:34.552 --> 00:01:37.347 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In fact, I recommended you
for the position myself.

40
00:01:37.430 --> 00:01:39.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Allow me to offer
my congratulations

41
00:01:39.766 --> 00:01:41.434 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to the new
Supreme Commander

42
00:01:41.518 --> 00:01:42.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
of the Ninth Fleet.

43
00:01:44.395 --> 00:01:46.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you have any idea
how much paperwork

44
00:01:46.731 --> 00:01:48.942 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a Supreme Commander
has to do?

45
00:01:49.025 --> 00:01:50.026 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're welcome.

46
00:01:50.110 --> 00:01:52.237 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>growls </i>)

47
00:01:52.320 --> 00:01:54.155 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
May I arrange quarters
for you on the station?

48
00:01:54.239 --> 00:01:57.742 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, I'll keep my flag
aboard the <i>Rotarran.</i>

49
00:01:57.826 --> 00:02:01.371 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It may be cramped but at least I'll feel
like I'm still in the war.

50
00:02:01.454 --> 00:02:04.457 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
By the way, I'd like Worf
to continue functioning

51
00:02:04.541 --> 00:02:06.334 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
as my principal
Intelligence Officer.

52
00:02:06.417 --> 00:02:08.336 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't see any problem
with that.

53
00:02:08.419 --> 00:02:11.381 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's the only officer I know
who can never get enough work.

54
00:02:11.464 --> 00:02:13.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>cackles </i>)

55
00:02:13.508 --> 00:02:15.051 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, at least if he's busy

56
00:02:15.135 --> 00:02:18.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
he'll stop going on
about this wedding of his.

57
00:02:19.764 --> 00:02:21.933 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, there were times
aboard the <i>Rotarran</i>

58
00:02:22.016 --> 00:02:23.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
he nearly drove me mad.

59
00:02:23.893 --> 00:02:26.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Until his son arrived,
it was all he could talk about.

60
00:02:27.021 --> 00:02:29.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then Alexander became
all he could talk about.

61
00:02:29.983 --> 00:02:33.444 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The man is nothing
if not single-minded.

62
00:02:33.528 --> 00:02:35.280 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I haven't met Worf's son yet.

63
00:02:35.363 --> 00:02:37.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's he like?

64
00:02:37.407 --> 00:02:39.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's a fine boy...

65
00:02:39.117 --> 00:02:41.703 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
dedicated, eager.

66
00:02:41.786 --> 00:02:44.622 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He has the heart
of his father

67
00:02:44.706 --> 00:02:48.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but he's not the best
soldier I've ever seen.

68
00:02:48.251 --> 00:02:50.628 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But when he ordered me
to bring the system back online,

69
00:02:50.712 --> 00:02:52.046 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought he was still talking

70
00:02:52.130 --> 00:02:54.632 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
about the hydro-static
system, so...

71
00:02:54.716 --> 00:02:55.842 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You didn't
engage the pumps

72
00:02:55.925 --> 00:02:57.510 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
while the check valves
were open.

73
00:02:57.594 --> 00:02:58.887 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He did.

74
00:02:58.970 --> 00:03:00.847 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I flooded
the entire deck

75
00:03:00.930 --> 00:03:02.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
with super-heated
hydraulic fluid.

76
00:03:02.807 --> 00:03:05.059 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It took me three days
to clean it up

77
00:03:05.143 --> 00:03:07.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but, I swear, it still smells
like burnt dog hair in there.

78
00:03:07.979 --> 00:03:11.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh! Remind me to keep you away
from the <i>Defiant. </i>You're a menace.

79
00:03:11.441 --> 00:03:14.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The <i>Rotarran's </i>crew actually thinks of me
as a good luck charm.

80
00:03:14.569 --> 00:03:19.699 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, the more mistakes
<i>I </i>make, the safer <i>they </i>feel.

81
00:03:19.782 --> 00:03:22.201 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hope the <i>Ya'Vang's crew</i>
feels the same way.

82
00:03:22.285 --> 00:03:23.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The <i>Ya'Vang?</i>

83
00:03:24.913 --> 00:03:27.123 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I got new orders this morning.

84
00:03:27.206 --> 00:03:29.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The battle cruiser <i>Ya'Vang</i>
took heavy losses

85
00:03:29.918 --> 00:03:31.628 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in their last engagement

86
00:03:31.711 --> 00:03:34.088 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so most of the <i>Rotarran's crew</i>
are being transferred there

87
00:03:34.172 --> 00:03:36.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
at the end of the week,
including me.

88
00:03:38.801 --> 00:03:41.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, more bloodwine?

89
00:03:41.304 --> 00:03:42.472 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why not?

90
00:03:42.555 --> 00:03:44.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No. Not for me.

91
00:03:46.351 --> 00:03:48.061 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Handsome young man.

92
00:03:48.144 --> 00:03:50.146 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He must get his looks
from his mother's side.

93
00:03:50.230 --> 00:03:51.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What do you want?

94
00:03:51.856 --> 00:03:55.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have you had a chance
to reconsider my offer?

95
00:03:55.318 --> 00:03:58.363 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We are not getting
married in this bar.

96
00:03:58.446 --> 00:04:00.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The ceremony will take place
on the Klingon homeworld

97
00:04:00.949 --> 00:04:02.158 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
after the war.

98
00:04:02.242 --> 00:04:05.245 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Worf, let's do it here,
this week

99
00:04:05.328 --> 00:04:06.621 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
before Alexander leaves.

100
00:04:06.704 --> 00:04:07.997 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
QUARK:
Perfect.

101
00:04:08.081 --> 00:04:09.290 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll handle
all the arrangements.

102
00:04:09.374 --> 00:04:12.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Wait. I thought
we had agreed.

103
00:04:12.085 --> 00:04:14.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We did, but I would hate
for Alexander

104
00:04:14.337 --> 00:04:15.463 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to miss
his father's wedding.

105
00:04:15.546 --> 00:04:18.049 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It would mean so much to him.

106
00:04:19.175 --> 00:04:22.053 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And besides,
it may be a long time

107
00:04:22.136 --> 00:04:24.055 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
before you see him again.

108
00:04:29.894 --> 00:04:32.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's going on?

109
00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:37.318 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our wedding plans
have changed.

110
00:04:37.402 --> 00:04:40.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We are getting married here
on Deep Space 9

111
00:04:40.488 --> 00:04:43.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I would like you
to be my <i>Tawi'Yan.</i>

112
00:04:47.078 --> 00:04:48.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Sword-bearer."

113
00:04:49.038 --> 00:04:51.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's sort of like
a best man.

114
00:04:51.624 --> 00:04:53.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me?

115
00:04:53.793 --> 00:04:55.044 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really?

116
00:04:55.128 --> 00:04:56.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, that's great!

117
00:04:56.129 --> 00:04:57.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>yelping </i>)

118
00:05:00.049 --> 00:05:02.051 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll put that
on your tab.

119
00:07:03.381 --> 00:07:04.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
DAX:
It doesn't leave much time

120
00:07:04.465 --> 00:07:05.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to make
all the arrangements

121
00:07:06.050 --> 00:07:08.052 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but fortunately, there isn't
that much left to do.

122
00:07:08.136 --> 00:07:09.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Worf's been planning
the ceremony

123
00:07:10.012 --> 00:07:11.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
for the last three months.

124
00:07:11.639 --> 00:07:13.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
He has everything
figured out

125
00:07:13.516 --> 00:07:15.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
right down
to the color of my shoes.

126
00:07:15.643 --> 00:07:18.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
No offense, Jadzia,
but it seems like this wedding's

127
00:07:18.521 --> 00:07:20.106 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
all about what Worf wants.

128
00:07:20.189 --> 00:07:22.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Uh, Habitat Ring,
Section 51 Gamma.

129
00:07:22.984 --> 00:07:24.986 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What about you?

130
00:07:25.069 --> 00:07:27.572 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
A traditional Klingon wedding
with all the trimmings

131
00:07:27.655 --> 00:07:30.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
is something Worf's
been thinking about since he was a boy.

132
00:07:30.700 --> 00:07:33.202 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
It probably has something
to do with being raised

133
00:07:33.286 --> 00:07:34.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
by human parents.

134
00:07:34.954 --> 00:07:36.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
In any case, when it comes
to Klingon tradition,

135
00:07:37.081 --> 00:07:38.207 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Worf is very sentimental.

136
00:07:38.291 --> 00:07:39.709 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Worf?

137
00:07:39.792 --> 00:07:41.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
All men are sentimental.

138
00:07:41.919 --> 00:07:45.465 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
They just cover it up with
scowls and clenched jaws.

139
00:07:45.548 --> 00:07:50.094 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
There are times when Worf
literally gets misty-eyed

140
00:07:50.178 --> 00:07:52.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
talking about
Klingon rituals.

141
00:07:53.556 --> 00:07:55.475 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
So, uh, that's
why you're letting him

142
00:07:55.558 --> 00:07:57.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
make the plans
for the wedding?

143
00:07:57.185 --> 00:07:59.312 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Mostly, but
the truth is

144
00:07:59.395 --> 00:08:00.646 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I've already
been through five

145
00:08:00.730 --> 00:08:01.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Trill ceremonies--

146
00:08:01.939 --> 00:08:03.483 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
three as a bride,
two as a groom,

147
00:08:03.566 --> 00:08:04.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
and I'm a little bored with it.

148
00:08:04.817 --> 00:08:06.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Is it my imagination

149
00:08:06.194 --> 00:08:07.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
or did Odo just
try and avoid us?

150
00:08:07.945 --> 00:08:09.197 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I didn't notice.

151
00:08:09.947 --> 00:08:11.073 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

152
00:08:11.157 --> 00:08:12.700 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
We've been avoiding
each other

153
00:08:12.783 --> 00:08:14.869 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
ever since the Dominion
left the station.

154
00:08:14.952 --> 00:08:16.496 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I think we're both
afraid of talking

155
00:08:16.579 --> 00:08:18.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
about what happened
during the occupation.

156
00:08:18.581 --> 00:08:20.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What do you mean?

157
00:08:21.042 --> 00:08:23.419 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Oh, to tell you the truth,

158
00:08:23.503 --> 00:08:26.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
it's nothing I want to talk
about right now either.

159
00:08:29.675 --> 00:08:31.052 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Thank you for coming.

160
00:08:31.135 --> 00:08:33.179 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
As you probably know by now,

161
00:08:33.262 --> 00:08:36.098 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Jadzia and I will be married
here on the station in six days.

162
00:08:36.182 --> 00:08:37.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's nothing
more romantic

163
00:08:37.767 --> 00:08:40.019 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
than a wedding on
DS9 in springtime.

164
00:08:40.102 --> 00:08:41.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When the neutrinos
are in bloom.

165
00:08:41.938 --> 00:08:45.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
By tradition,
the Klingon man spends

166
00:08:45.233 --> 00:08:46.526 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the four nights
before his wedding

167
00:08:46.609 --> 00:08:48.861 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
on a mental
and spiritual journey.

168
00:08:48.945 --> 00:08:52.156 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is called <i>Kal'Hyah,</i>
"The Path of Clarity"

169
00:08:52.240 --> 00:08:56.202 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and </i>he is accompanied
by his closest male friends.

170
00:08:56.285 --> 00:08:58.746 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You cannot imagine
the experience that awaits us--

171
00:08:58.829 --> 00:09:03.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
four long nights filled
with song and fellowship.

172
00:09:03.376 --> 00:09:05.711 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A time of unbridled pleasures.

173
00:09:05.795 --> 00:09:08.673 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are we talking
about a bachelor party here?

174
00:09:08.756 --> 00:09:11.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It is a similar ritual.

175
00:09:11.175 --> 00:09:12.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sounds good to me.

176
00:09:12.843 --> 00:09:14.262 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me, too.

177
00:09:14.345 --> 00:09:16.013 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Count me in.

178
00:09:16.097 --> 00:09:17.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We will meet
in the holosuite

179
00:09:17.640 --> 00:09:19.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
tomorrow night
at 2100 hours.

180
00:09:19.433 --> 00:09:21.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
MARTOK: I advise you all
to get plenty of rest.

181
00:09:21.561 --> 00:09:23.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Four nights
at a Klingon bachelor party.

182
00:09:23.896 --> 00:09:25.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just think of
the possibilities.

183
00:09:25.481 --> 00:09:26.566 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thank God
Keiko's not here.

184
00:09:26.649 --> 00:09:27.984 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wonder what Dax
will be doing

185
00:09:28.067 --> 00:09:30.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
while we're traveling
down <i>Kal'Hyah.</i>

186
00:09:30.278 --> 00:09:32.655 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She will be taking
a different journey...

187
00:09:32.738 --> 00:09:34.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
with my wife.

188
00:09:36.158 --> 00:09:37.577 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Your wife?

189
00:09:42.832 --> 00:09:44.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
By marrying Worf,

190
00:09:44.166 --> 00:09:46.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dax will be joining
the House of Martok.

191
00:09:46.335 --> 00:09:48.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Since the mistress
of a great House

192
00:09:48.129 --> 00:09:49.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
must approve all marriages,

193
00:09:49.797 --> 00:09:51.173 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sirella will spend
the next four days

194
00:09:51.257 --> 00:09:52.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
evaluating Jadzia.

195
00:10:01.183 --> 00:10:02.935 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My lady.

196
00:10:03.019 --> 00:10:05.771 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You've put on weight...

197
00:10:05.855 --> 00:10:08.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and your hair is going gray.

198
00:10:09.358 --> 00:10:14.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My deterioration
is proceeding apace.

199
00:10:14.280 --> 00:10:17.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought you would be
in your grave by now.

200
00:10:17.366 --> 00:10:18.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>chuckling </i>)

201
00:10:18.451 --> 00:10:20.328 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I shall endeavor to die--

202
00:10:20.411 --> 00:10:22.163 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
this year, if possible.

203
00:10:22.246 --> 00:10:25.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Allow me to present
Captain Benjamin Sisko,

204
00:10:25.124 --> 00:10:27.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander of Deep Space 9.

205
00:10:27.084 --> 00:10:29.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Captain, may I present

206
00:10:29.128 --> 00:10:31.964 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the mistress of the House
of Martok, my wife

207
00:10:32.048 --> 00:10:33.841 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the mother
of my children...

208
00:10:33.924 --> 00:10:36.510 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sirella, daughter of Linkasa.

209
00:10:36.594 --> 00:10:39.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Welcome to
Deep Space 9.

210
00:10:39.305 --> 00:10:41.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you, Captain.

211
00:10:41.474 --> 00:10:42.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where is she?

212
00:10:42.892 --> 00:10:45.436 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Jadzia's quarters
are in the Habitat Ring,

213
00:10:45.519 --> 00:10:48.272 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Section... 25 Alpha.

214
00:10:48.356 --> 00:10:49.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shall I escort you?

215
00:10:49.607 --> 00:10:51.067 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's quite far away.

216
00:10:51.150 --> 00:10:52.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll find my way.

217
00:10:56.280 --> 00:10:57.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you'll excuse me.

218
00:11:01.577 --> 00:11:04.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Magnificent, isn't she?

219
00:11:13.672 --> 00:11:16.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are those real
<i>var'Hama </i>candles?

220
00:11:16.634 --> 00:11:18.803 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes, Worf,
I traveled to Kronos.

221
00:11:18.886 --> 00:11:21.847 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I captured three <i>targs</i>
in the Hamar mountains,

222
00:11:21.931 --> 00:11:23.307 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
made the ritual
sacrifice at dawn,

223
00:11:23.391 --> 00:11:25.393 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
came back
to the station,

224
00:11:25.476 --> 00:11:27.603 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
asked Quark to boil their
shoulders into tallow.

225
00:11:27.686 --> 00:11:31.023 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then, I spent two days
molding them into candles

226
00:11:31.107 --> 00:11:32.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
with my own hands.

227
00:11:32.233 --> 00:11:34.402 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was just asking.

228
00:11:34.485 --> 00:11:37.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You were
criticizing <i>again.</i>

229
00:11:38.030 --> 00:11:40.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Relax. She's not
going to reject

230
00:11:40.699 --> 00:11:42.034 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a prospective daughter

231
00:11:42.118 --> 00:11:43.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because the
<i>var'Hama </i>candles

232
00:11:43.452 --> 00:11:44.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in her welcoming
display were replicated.

233
00:11:45.037 --> 00:11:45.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>door chimes </i>)

234
00:11:46.038 --> 00:11:47.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come in.

235
00:11:52.962 --> 00:11:55.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Tug son bosh mok</i>
<i>A'Beh, Sirella koH.</i>

236
00:11:56.048 --> 00:11:57.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>E'Gagh vet moh.</i>

237
00:11:58.509 --> 00:12:00.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is <i>he </i>doing here?

238
00:12:00.845 --> 00:12:02.805 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I meant no disrespect.

239
00:12:02.888 --> 00:12:03.973 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then leave.

240
00:12:12.648 --> 00:12:16.402 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your worthiness to join
our House will now be judged

241
00:12:16.485 --> 00:12:18.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
according to the traditions
of my family.

242
00:12:18.904 --> 00:12:20.197 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am prepared, my lady.

243
00:12:20.281 --> 00:12:22.116 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I doubt that.

244
00:12:22.199 --> 00:12:26.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A Klingon woman would find it
difficult to gain my favor.

245
00:12:26.704 --> 00:12:29.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
For...an <i>alien,</i>

246
00:12:29.415 --> 00:12:31.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
it will most likely
be impossible.

247
00:12:31.709 --> 00:12:33.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I like a challenge.

248
00:12:33.335 --> 00:12:37.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I will not have my authority
challenged by you.

249
00:12:37.840 --> 00:12:39.675 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's not what I meant.

250
00:12:39.758 --> 00:12:42.803 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you cannot say what you mean,
say nothing at all.

251
00:12:44.305 --> 00:12:47.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The evaluation
will begin tomorrow morning.

252
00:12:47.224 --> 00:12:51.020 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have the traditional meal
prepared before I arrive.

253
00:12:52.897 --> 00:12:54.690 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And in the future,

254
00:12:54.773 --> 00:12:58.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if you cannot trouble yourself
to make real <i>var'Hama </i>candles,

255
00:12:58.652 --> 00:13:02.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
try not to use
such obvious fakes.

256
00:13:18.088 --> 00:13:20.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You never told me that your wife
was opposed to this marriage.

257
00:13:20.799 --> 00:13:22.801 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sirella is a woman
of strong convictions.

258
00:13:22.885 --> 00:13:24.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She believes
that by bringing aliens

259
00:13:24.762 --> 00:13:27.264 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
into our families,
we risk losing our identity

260
00:13:27.348 --> 00:13:28.641 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
as Klingons.

261
00:13:28.724 --> 00:13:30.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That is a prejudiced,
xenophobic view.

262
00:13:30.643 --> 00:13:32.645 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We <i>are </i>Klingons, Worf.

263
00:13:32.728 --> 00:13:36.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We don't <i>embrace </i>other cultures.
We <i>conquer </i>them.

264
00:13:36.524 --> 00:13:39.860 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If someone wishes to join us,
they must honor our traditions

265
00:13:39.944 --> 00:13:41.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and prove themselves worthy

266
00:13:41.654 --> 00:13:44.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of wearing the crest
of a Great House.

267
00:13:44.198 --> 00:13:45.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jadzia <i>is </i>worthy.

268
00:13:45.616 --> 00:13:47.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course she is.

269
00:13:47.535 --> 00:13:50.621 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She's an honorable woman
and a formidable warrior.

270
00:13:50.704 --> 00:13:53.207 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You should say <i>that </i>to Sirella.

271
00:13:54.458 --> 00:13:55.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's not such a good idea.

272
00:13:55.876 --> 00:13:58.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't want her to think

273
00:13:58.128 --> 00:14:02.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that I'm interfering
in her domain.

274
00:14:02.508 --> 00:14:04.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Perhaps I should
speak with her.

275
00:14:04.760 --> 00:14:07.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Coming from me, it would
not seem like a challenge

276
00:14:07.638 --> 00:14:08.889 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to her authority.

277
00:14:08.973 --> 00:14:10.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wouldn't do that
if I were you.

278
00:14:12.560 --> 00:14:13.727 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why?

279
00:14:14.853 --> 00:14:16.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, um...

280
00:14:16.689 --> 00:14:19.483 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the truth is...

281
00:14:19.567 --> 00:14:21.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
she doesn't like you
that much either.

282
00:14:21.819 --> 00:14:23.571 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me.

283
00:14:23.654 --> 00:14:25.656 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't let that
bother you.

284
00:14:25.739 --> 00:14:28.534 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I had every right
to bring you into the family

285
00:14:28.617 --> 00:14:30.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and she's accepted the fact

286
00:14:30.452 --> 00:14:33.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that there's <i>nothing</i>
she can do about it.

287
00:14:33.205 --> 00:14:34.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How comforting.

288
00:14:35.958 --> 00:14:36.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>chuckles </i>)

289
00:14:36.959 --> 00:14:40.087 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>laughing </i>)

290
00:14:40.170 --> 00:14:43.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And they say that
you have no sense of humor.

291
00:14:44.008 --> 00:14:47.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>laughing </i>)

292
00:15:01.275 --> 00:15:03.694 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Phew. I could do
without the heat.

293
00:15:03.777 --> 00:15:06.363 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can't, uh, say much
for the decor either.

294
00:15:06.447 --> 00:15:08.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, it can't be
<i>all </i>fun and games.

295
00:15:08.949 --> 00:15:12.202 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sure there has to be
some sort of ritual

296
00:15:12.286 --> 00:15:15.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we have to go through
before the party begins.

297
00:15:15.414 --> 00:15:18.334 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There <i>is </i>going to be
a party, isn't there?

298
00:15:18.417 --> 00:15:19.919 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're asking me?

299
00:15:20.002 --> 00:15:22.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can barely say
my name in Klingon.

300
00:15:23.047 --> 00:15:25.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
MARTOK:
Prepare yourselves, my friends

301
00:15:26.008 --> 00:15:28.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
for a journey
you won't soon forget.

302
00:15:34.016 --> 00:15:35.392 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
These...

303
00:15:35.476 --> 00:15:36.936 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
are <i>Ma'Stakas.</i>

304
00:15:37.019 --> 00:15:38.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What, uh, what do
we do with them?

305
00:15:38.938 --> 00:15:41.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
At the conclusion
of the wedding ceremony

306
00:15:41.440 --> 00:15:43.817 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you will use them
to attack Worf and Dax.

307
00:15:43.901 --> 00:15:45.444 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Obviously.
Don't you know anything?

308
00:15:45.527 --> 00:15:46.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The tradition dates back

309
00:15:46.946 --> 00:15:48.864 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to the wedding
of Kahless and Lukara

310
00:15:48.948 --> 00:15:50.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who were nearly killed
by Molor's troops

311
00:15:50.699 --> 00:15:52.034 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
moments after they were
married.

312
00:15:52.117 --> 00:15:53.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Until the ceremony,

313
00:15:53.827 --> 00:15:55.245 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you should keep these with you
at all times.

314
00:15:55.329 --> 00:15:56.789 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
SISKO:
I trust

315
00:15:56.872 --> 00:15:59.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
this combat is non-lethal.

316
00:15:59.458 --> 00:16:01.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is a symbolic
attack only.

317
00:16:02.044 --> 00:16:03.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh.

318
00:16:05.381 --> 00:16:07.675 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That food is not
to be eaten.

319
00:16:09.176 --> 00:16:10.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then what is it for?

320
00:16:10.552 --> 00:16:13.472 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is there to tempt us
to break our fast.

321
00:16:13.555 --> 00:16:14.765 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Fast?

322
00:16:14.848 --> 00:16:16.183 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There are six trials

323
00:16:16.266 --> 00:16:18.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we must face
on the path to <i>Kal'Hyah.</i>

324
00:16:18.852 --> 00:16:21.146 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is the first--
deprivation.

325
00:16:21.230 --> 00:16:23.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We now begin a fast
that will continue

326
00:16:23.440 --> 00:16:25.025 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
until the day of the wedding.

327
00:16:25.109 --> 00:16:26.902 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, th-that's
four days away.

328
00:16:26.986 --> 00:16:28.445 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
MARTOK:
It is a short time,

329
00:16:28.529 --> 00:16:30.280 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know, but we must
make the best of it.

330
00:16:30.364 --> 00:16:33.492 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What are
the other five trials?

331
00:16:33.575 --> 00:16:37.079 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Blood, pain, sacrifice,
anguish...

332
00:16:37.162 --> 00:16:38.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and death.

333
00:16:38.330 --> 00:16:40.249 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sounds like marriage,
all right.

334
00:16:40.332 --> 00:16:41.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How would you know?

335
00:16:41.333 --> 00:16:42.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It is time to begin.

336
00:16:48.507 --> 00:16:50.509 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
QUARK:
Need more flowers on the banister.

337
00:16:50.592 --> 00:16:52.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
MALE: We're ready
with the banner, boss.

338
00:16:52.261 --> 00:16:53.429 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>whistles </i>)

339
00:16:53.512 --> 00:16:54.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Raise it.

340
00:16:54.680 --> 00:16:56.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're up early.

341
00:16:56.515 --> 00:16:57.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought writers
slept late.

342
00:16:57.891 --> 00:16:59.059 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not always.

343
00:16:59.143 --> 00:17:00.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I sold my first
book today.

344
00:17:00.853 --> 00:17:03.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Really? How much
did you get for it?

345
00:17:03.689 --> 00:17:05.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's just a
figure of speech.

346
00:17:05.399 --> 00:17:06.859 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Federation
News Service

347
00:17:06.942 --> 00:17:08.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is going to publish
a book of my stories

348
00:17:08.569 --> 00:17:09.820 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
about life on the station
under Dominion rule.

349
00:17:09.903 --> 00:17:11.530 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And they're not
paying you?

350
00:17:11.613 --> 00:17:12.781 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No.

351
00:17:12.865 --> 00:17:14.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, then you have
my sympathies

352
00:17:14.658 --> 00:17:16.493 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the first round
of drinks is on the house.

353
00:17:16.577 --> 00:17:17.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really?

354
00:17:17.745 --> 00:17:20.956 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No. It's a figure
of speech.

355
00:17:21.040 --> 00:17:22.624 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Look, I want to tell
my dad about the book.

356
00:17:22.708 --> 00:17:24.084 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Is he still in
the holosuite?

357
00:17:24.168 --> 00:17:27.004 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, yeah.
They're still up there.

358
00:17:27.087 --> 00:17:28.964 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are they doing?

359
00:17:29.048 --> 00:17:31.467 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's a Klingon
bachelor party.

360
00:17:33.927 --> 00:17:35.095 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're a writer.

361
00:17:35.179 --> 00:17:37.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Use your imagination.

362
00:17:39.933 --> 00:17:41.852 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
BASHIR:
Alexander.

363
00:17:43.145 --> 00:17:44.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Grandma?

364
00:17:45.022 --> 00:17:46.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Guess again.

365
00:17:50.110 --> 00:17:51.445 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're still on the...?

366
00:17:51.528 --> 00:17:55.532 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The road to <i>Kal'Hyah,</i>
day 500.

367
00:17:55.616 --> 00:17:57.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe we should
turn down the heat

368
00:17:57.743 --> 00:17:59.578 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you know, for
Alexander's sake.

369
00:17:59.661 --> 00:18:01.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, no, it's okay.
I, uh...

370
00:18:01.955 --> 00:18:04.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I just need some water.

371
00:18:04.958 --> 00:18:07.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, you don't want
to push yourself too hard.

372
00:18:07.878 --> 00:18:11.632 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, turning down the heat
might be a good idea.

373
00:18:12.591 --> 00:18:14.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The whole point
is to push yourself

374
00:18:14.802 --> 00:18:17.471 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to the limits
of your endurance.

375
00:18:19.098 --> 00:18:21.058 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>panting </i>)

376
00:18:22.392 --> 00:18:23.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I will.

377
00:18:23.977 --> 00:18:27.189 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I want to travel
the entire path to <i>Kal'Hyah.</i>

378
00:18:27.272 --> 00:18:29.441 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stoke the fire again!

379
00:18:29.525 --> 00:18:31.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
As you wish.

380
00:18:31.568 --> 00:18:37.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Of course, we cannot expect
you non-Klingons to...

381
00:18:37.449 --> 00:18:39.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
have the same stamina
as we do.

382
00:18:39.910 --> 00:18:42.246 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you wish to quit,
no one will think

383
00:18:42.329 --> 00:18:43.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
any less of you.

384
00:18:43.664 --> 00:18:45.290 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Who said anything
about quitting?

385
00:18:45.374 --> 00:18:47.209 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not me.

386
00:18:47.292 --> 00:18:49.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I like the heat.

387
00:18:49.545 --> 00:18:51.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's the spirit.

388
00:18:53.423 --> 00:18:55.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>Kaaa vek ko lee ko </i>♪

389
00:18:55.676 --> 00:18:58.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>eh to che maH lo </i>♪

390
00:18:58.470 --> 00:19:03.267 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
♪ <i>TaH oo-wah kaH esh to</i>
<i>pah deH ah reee! </i>♪

391
00:19:03.350 --> 00:19:06.061 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>YaH Bosh-ah! </i>♪

392
00:19:06.145 --> 00:19:08.480 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>YaH Bosh-ah! </i>♪

393
00:19:08.564 --> 00:19:11.066 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>YaH Bosh tomaH! </i>♪

394
00:19:11.150 --> 00:19:12.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Al'qoch</i>

395
00:19:12.526 --> 00:19:13.652 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>mensaH</i>

396
00:19:13.735 --> 00:19:14.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>t'lang</i>

397
00:19:14.736 --> 00:19:15.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>cho.</i>

398
00:19:19.366 --> 00:19:20.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Again.

399
00:19:21.827 --> 00:19:24.163 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've done it
three times already.

400
00:19:24.246 --> 00:19:26.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You continue
to rush through the ceremony,

401
00:19:27.082 --> 00:19:29.668 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
your body
position is poor,

402
00:19:29.751 --> 00:19:31.670 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the placement
of the braziers

403
00:19:31.753 --> 00:19:34.631 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
on their pedestals
is sloppy.

404
00:19:37.676 --> 00:19:40.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you know how heavy
those things are?

405
00:19:40.721 --> 00:19:43.307 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A Klingon woman
would not complain.

406
00:19:43.390 --> 00:19:45.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You wouldn't make
a Klingon woman

407
00:19:45.601 --> 00:19:46.727 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
do it three times in a row.

408
00:19:46.810 --> 00:19:48.312 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wouldn't have to.

409
00:19:48.395 --> 00:19:50.397 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She'd have done it correctly
the first time.

410
00:19:54.193 --> 00:19:55.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
End this now, Jadzia.

411
00:19:55.986 --> 00:19:58.363 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Go back to your own people.

412
00:19:58.447 --> 00:20:00.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They will tolerate
your weaknesses

413
00:20:00.991 --> 00:20:03.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and your failings
in a way that a Klingon family

414
00:20:03.911 --> 00:20:05.579 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
never will.

415
00:20:05.662 --> 00:20:09.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In our House, you would
always be an alien--

416
00:20:09.291 --> 00:20:11.460 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
an outsider.

417
00:20:11.543 --> 00:20:13.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
At best, you'd be
an object of pity

418
00:20:13.128 --> 00:20:15.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but you'd never
be accepted

419
00:20:15.464 --> 00:20:16.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
never an equal

420
00:20:17.007 --> 00:20:20.510 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because you can never
truly be one of us.

421
00:20:27.434 --> 00:20:30.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ko'ma tlang'goS ak-bay</i>

422
00:20:30.229 --> 00:20:34.066 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Hava'dak croosh tovaH</i>

423
00:20:34.149 --> 00:20:35.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ko'ma Kahless</i>

424
00:20:36.026 --> 00:20:38.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ko'ma Kahless</i>

425
00:20:38.487 --> 00:20:41.490 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ko'ma Kahless.</i>

426
00:20:50.123 --> 00:20:53.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But the Second Dynasty ended
when General K'Trelan

427
00:20:53.335 --> 00:20:55.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
assassinated Emperor Reclaw.

428
00:20:55.420 --> 00:20:58.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
For the next ten years,
the Empire was ruled

429
00:20:58.465 --> 00:21:00.634 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
by a Council elected
by the people.

430
00:21:00.717 --> 00:21:02.928 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Modern-day
Klingon historians

431
00:21:03.011 --> 00:21:05.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
refer to this
as "The Dark Time."

432
00:21:05.639 --> 00:21:09.935 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But it's interesting to note
that this first and only

433
00:21:10.018 --> 00:21:11.603 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
experiment
in Klingon democracy

434
00:21:11.687 --> 00:21:14.231 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
actually produced
several reforms...

435
00:21:14.314 --> 00:21:16.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You are straying from the saga.

436
00:21:16.316 --> 00:21:17.818 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Am I?

437
00:21:19.152 --> 00:21:22.823 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your task is to recite
the complete chronicle

438
00:21:22.906 --> 00:21:24.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
of the women in my family.

439
00:21:24.992 --> 00:21:26.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I just thought I'd give you

440
00:21:26.702 --> 00:21:29.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a broader historical perspective
along the way.

441
00:21:29.538 --> 00:21:33.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I am familiar
with Klingon history.

442
00:21:33.292 --> 00:21:38.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, return to the story
of my 23rd maternal grandmother

443
00:21:38.755 --> 00:21:41.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Shenara,
daughter of Emperor Reclaw

444
00:21:41.842 --> 00:21:43.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in the Second Dynasty.

445
00:21:43.677 --> 00:21:47.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, that's where we run
into a little bit of a problem.

446
00:21:47.097 --> 00:21:49.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You see, I did some research

447
00:21:49.266 --> 00:21:51.518 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and when Emperor Reclaw
was killed,

448
00:21:51.601 --> 00:21:54.187 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
all of the members
of the Imperial Family

449
00:21:54.271 --> 00:21:56.690 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
